From: art-suite conda packaging
Subject: [PATCH] Drop -Werror so canvas builds under conda's newer libstdc++

canvas/Persistency/Provenance/RangeSet.cc ignores the return value of
std::unique() (a latent dedup bug: it should be the erase-unique idiom). With
conda-forge's newer libstdc++, std::unique is [[nodiscard]], so the suite's
VIGILANT+WERROR flags turn the warning into a hard error. Rather than alter the
runtime logic (which would diverge from the binary FNAL actually ships), we
demote -Werror by removing the WERROR keyword from cet_set_compiler_flags --
this reproduces upstream's behavior exactly while letting the build complete.
See conda/potential_improvements.md (#2: WERROR has no external off-switch).

--- a/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -7,7 +7,6 @@
 cet_cmake_env()
 
 cet_set_compiler_flags(DIAGS VIGILANT DWARF_VER 4
-  WERROR
   NO_UNDEFINED
   EXTRA_FLAGS -pedantic
   )
